    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>
                <date>Feby 13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1834</date>
            </p>
            <p>Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have postponed writing to you, <sic>untill</sic>
                <persName>Mr Block</persName><lb/> went on, but as it is now a matter of doubt
                whether he will<lb/> go at all, I will not longer delay altho' I can with
                difficulty<lb/> hold my pen as I have a very sore fingerâ€”indeed my dear<lb/> fellow,
                I am very much at a loss for a subject, for sentimental<lb/> letters I write more,
                local matter would be uninteresting<lb/> &amp; Political I do not understand, yet I
                could manage to <add>?</add><lb/> your attention for a few minutes I suppose could I
                bring<lb/> myself once more to like letter writing, but really after<lb/> having
                written three letters, one to <persName>Aunt Leixa<add>?</add></persName>
                <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> to <persName>Mrs Spotswood</persName> &amp;
                    <persName>Miss Ettings</persName>, I am <sic>hartily</sic> tired of<lb/> the
                business; however to begin something we have received<lb/> your Books, and I am very
                much pleased with it,<lb/> I am almost ashamed to confess that I did not get<lb/>
                through with the first copy sent as I found much<lb/> difficulty in
                    <sic>peacing</sic> them together and the children<lb/> would bother and pull
                them about so that I got<lb/> impatient and awaited its arrival in a more<lb/>
                tangible form, and I do request you not to trouble<lb/> yourself to send me <hi
                    rend="underline">your next</hi> production <sic>untill</sic> it<lb/> is
                completed for it would be useless trouble, as I<lb/> can read so little at the time,
                I wish to find the peace</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>at which I last left off with the greatest case, I have<lb/> mentioned you &amp; your
                work to <persName>Mrs Spotswood</persName>, and I presume<lb/> she would like to
                procure a copy I should be pleased were<lb/> it to get in such able hands, I do not
                know the number<lb/> of copies sold, <persName>Mr B.</persName> will write you of
                them when dispo<lb/>sed of, the Jews here are like they are elsewhere rather<lb/>
                read any thing, understand any thing sooner than their<lb/> religion. I hear
                    <persName>Seixas Nathan</persName>, is broke for a million<lb/> of Dollars, is
                it really true? <sic>let</sic> me know when you<lb/> next write all you know of the
                matterâ€”what<lb/> was the <sic>occation</sic> of <persName>Miss Cohen's</persName>
                death do you know?<lb/> I was very much shocked to hear itâ€”are you better<lb/> I
                heard you had been sick, I think <persName>Isaac</persName> a<lb/> trip this way
                would be of service to you the sight of<lb/> old friends better than medicine
                suppose you try<lb/> it and let me have the pleasure of seeing you soon<lb/> I have
                a room at your disposal, and you could<lb/> be as much retired when you wish as you
                    <add>?</add><lb/> indeed I'm sure <sic>travelling</sic> over the mountains<lb/>
                would be of great service to you and I should be<lb/> delighted to see you at my
                houseâ€”your old friend<lb/>
                <persName>Eleanor</persName> is quite well, her husband is with you before this<lb/>
                <persName>Mrs Marks</persName> a family are also well and desire<lb/>
                remembranceâ€”Present me to all <sic>enquiring</sic> friends</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>I don't feel like writing any more and my<lb/> finger refuses to hold the pen any
                longer so<lb/> adieu your friend</p>
            <p><persName role="author">AB</persName>__</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">single</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revrd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
